This Present Darkness is a gripping story that brings keen insight into spiritual warfare and the necessity of prayer. Since its original publication more than 2.7 million copies have been sold. The companion volume, Piercing the Darkness, continues the story of the battle between spiritual forces.', 'In the quiet town of Ashton, a reporter and pastor uncover a demonic conspiracy tied to New Age influences, sparking intense spiritual warfare.', 1986, '8385435026', '9780829712131', 504, NULL, 1048, 'https://covers.openlibrary.org/b/id/842138-L.jpg', '/works/OL26292665W', NULL, 'Jan 11, 1990', 'English', NULL, 1, 0, 'this-present-darkness-frank-e-peretti', 0, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, 'public', '2026-03-16 05:40:53', '2026-03-22 20:32:05');
