Ellison draws on his early experiences - his father''s death when he was three; hoboing his way on a freight train to Tuskegee Institute to follow his early dreams of becoming a musician - to create stories that, according to The Washington Post, "approach the simple elegance of Chekhov."', NULL, 1998, '0679776613', NULL, 173, NULL, NULL, 'https://covers.openlibrary.org/b/id/419137-L.jpg', '/works/OL495471W', NULL, '1998', 'English', NULL, 1, 0, 'flying-home-and-other-stories-ralph-ellison', 0, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, 'import_only', '2026-03-16 05:43:24', '2026-03-25 00:23:59');
